  "texts": [
    "This graph data structure bakes into itself some deduction rules explicitly stated in the geometric rule list used in DD.",
    "These deduction rules from the original list are therefore not used anywhere in exploration but implicitly used and explicitly spelled out on-demand when the final proof is serialized into text.",
    "Traceback to find minimal proofs.",
    "Each deduction step needs to be coupled with a traceback algorithm, which returns the minimal set of immediate ancestor statements that is necessary to deduce the conclusion statement of the step.",
    "This is the core building block for extracting proof graphs and minimal premises described in the main text."
